<tr class="odd">
<td data-valign="top"><p>LECTURE VIII</p>
<p>THE DIVIDED SELF, AND THE PROCESS OF ITS UNIFICATION</p></td>
<td data-valign="bottom"><p><a href="vre08.htm#page_163">163</a></p></td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td data-valign="top"><p>Heterogeneous personality—Character gradually attains unity—Examples of divided self—The unity attained need not be religious—"Counter conversion" cases—Other cases—Gradual and sudden unification—Tolstoy's recovery—Bunyan's.</p></td>
<td data-valign="bottom"><p> </p></td>
</tr>
